%N A385187 Area of the unique primitive Pythagorean triple (a,b,c) such that (a-b+c)/2 = A002378(n) and its long leg and hypotenuse are consecutive natural numbers.
%C A385187 a(n) is a multiple of 6 for all n.
%H A385187 José-Miguel Blanco Casado and Miguel-Ángel Pérez García-Ortega, <a href="/A382844/a382844.pdf">El Libro de las Ternas Pitagóricas</a>
%F A385187 a(n) = (A385022(n,1) * A385022(n,2))/2.
%F A385187 a(n) = A002378(n)*(A002378(n) - 1)*(2*A002378(n) - 1).
%e A385187 For n=2, the short leg is A385022(2,1) = 11 and the long leg is A385022(2,2) = 60  so the area is then a(2) = (11 * 60)/2 = 330.
%t A385187 a=Table[n(n+1),{n,1,30}];Apply[Join,Map[{#(#-1)(2#-1)}&,a]]
